Ed,<br><br>
Glad to see you at max collective and gaining altitude.  Full load of ordinance and ready to play, I assume.  Pick a target and kick ass.  I got you covered.<br><br>
You know General George Crook who was Custers commander and considered him an idiot said the plains Indian was pound for pound the greatest fighting man he had ever seen.  There only weakness was they believed the white man and never told a lie or broke a promise.  Custer found out they didn't think much of a man without honor either.<br><br>
Ed do you believe a warriors spirit is in his weapons?  I do I can feel it.  I have a large colletion of weapons (old ones)  I have a Star 54cal carbine and a Smith 50cal carbine from your grandmother's land.  Both were used in the war.  You can feel the power when you close your eyes and dream.  I have a white mans 73 Winchester from the same period and the power is not the same.  Think I  am nuts.  Maybe, but I don't think so.<br><br>
You should hold a 500 year old Samuri long sword.  Awesome.<br><br>
Gee I am going to get sentimental.  You know how we are.<br><br>
Hang around and enjoy yourself.  I am
